# Alliance affairs (in-game mechanics)

HQ models **in-game** alliance mechanics separately from **HQ RBAC** and Ashed iframe pages.

## Server time

- Game server time is **UTC−2**.
- Calendar weeks start **Monday 00:00** server time.
- VS match week runs **Mon–Sat**; **Sunday off** (break day — no daily VS).

## Ranks R1–R5

- Stored in immutable `member_alliance_rank_events`; confirmed changes dual-write to Ashed `Member` and update `alliance_members`.
- Train pools (`r3`, `r4_plus`) read **local roster + rank-as-of date**, not live Ashed rank queries on every roll.
- **HQ RBAC** (owner/maintainer/officer) is unrelated to in-game R1–R5.

## Daily train ritual

| Role | Rule |
|------|------|
| **Conductor** | One per game day; guaranteed one of each item on the train when locked |
| **VIP** | Conductor may pick VIP; VIP chooses 2 of 4 rider cars; guaranteed one of each item in those cars |
| **Guardian** | Defends train on plunder — **VIP squads if `guardianIsVip`**, else Conductor squads |
| **Lock** | Spawns empty train (5 cars × 6 slots); **final** once locked (override = exceptional + audited) |

## Week templates & mechanisms

Stored on `train_day_configs`: `conductorMechanism`, `vipMechanism`, optional configs (`eventKey`, `topN`).

| Template | Typical conductor | Typical VIP |
|----------|-------------------|-------------|
| **vs_push_week** | Tue/Fri: `vs_high_score`; Wed/Thu/Sat: `vs_top_10`; Sun–Mon: `r4_sequence` | Tue–Sat: `conductor_pick`; Sun/Mon: `event_top_x_lottery` |
| **economy_week** / **r3_recognition** | `r3_lottery` | `conductor_pick` |
| **r4_train_week** | `r4_sequence` | `conductor_pick` |
| **donations_week** | `donations_top` | `donations_second` |

Composite templates (`vs_push_weekdays` + `r4_event_vip`) paint weekend segments via `conductorConfig.paintTemplate`.

## VS scoring for wheels

- `vs_top_10` and event pool seeding use **T−1** calendar day scores (`vsScoreReferenceDate(trainDate)` → Ashed `VSScore.recorded_date`).
- VS day names (Mon–Sat): Radar Training, Base Expansion, Age of Science, Hero Day, Total Mobilization, Buster Day.

## VS Performance video upload (daily vs weekly)

- **Daily** `recorded_date`: Mon–Sat match day (server calendar).
- **Weekly** `recorded_date`: the **Sunday** that ends that VS week (“week ending Sunday”). Sunday is not a match day; it is the week-end marker for totals.
- **Weekly upload window:** Sunday **00:00** → Monday **00:00** server time. An upload in that window may be treated as the weekly totals video for the week ending that Sunday (when no weekly batch exists yet). Officer-local Saturday night often falls in this window.
- Defaults and period toggles must use **`getServerCalendarDate` / `defaultVsPerformanceRecordedDate`**, never the officer’s account-local “today” alone — account Sat + server Sun otherwise snaps weekly to the **previous** Sunday.

## Economy-week pivot

Leadership may pivot Tue–Sun to economy-style (`r3_lottery`) after assessing Day 1 VS.

- **Pivot window:** Mon **22:00** – Tue **12:00** server time (UTC−2). Helper: `isWithinPivotWindow()` in `game-time.ts`.
- Paint **individual days** with `economy_week` → `train_day_configs.is_override = 1`; `recomputeWeekPivotFlag` sets `train_week_schedules.is_pivot`.
- Do **not** use whole-week `setWeekTemplate` alone for pivot — it can wipe per-day overrides.

## Pool exhaustion

- Lottery/sequence pools (`r3`, `r4_plus`, `event_top_x`) remove a member once selected for a date.
- When the last eligible member is picked, auto **re-seed** a new generation (`refreshExhaustedPoolIfNeeded`).
- **`r4_sequence`:** when pool not exhausted, assign **next in sequence** (no random wheel animation).
- Permanent **`train_conductor_records`** = alliance audit trail (conductor + VIP + lock time).

## Event VIP (`event_top_x_lottery`)

- `vipConfig.eventKey`: `capitol_war`, `meteorite_war` (default `capitol_war`).
- Event top scorers fetched from Ashed **`KillScore`** when available; falls back to dated **`VSScore`** if entity unknown.

## Native vs Ashed alliances

| Path | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| Pools / ranks | Local roster + rank events only (no Ashed PUT on rank sync) |
| VS / donation / event auto-rolls | Require Ashed connection — native alliances use **manual pick** or roster pool mechanisms |
| First visit | Empty roster → empty state; no phantom week schedule |

## API guardrails

- Train mutations: `requireTrainOfficer` (`trains:write`); reads tenant-scoped by session alliance.
- Reject schedule paint on dates with `lockedAt` set (409).
- Season override: `PATCH /api/alliance/season` (`alliance:admin` only) — not on trains page.
